  "prompt": "What is the amount of Maximum cash deposit in a saving bank account in a single financial year in India?",
  "response": "There is no specific limit on the maximum amount of cash you can deposit in a savings account in a single financial year in India.\n\nHowever, keep the following important points in mind:\n\n*   **Reporting Requirements:** Banks are required to report certain cash transactions to the Income Tax Department. For savings accounts, cash deposits totaling \u20b910 lakh or more in a financial year are reported.\n\n*   **Scrutiny by the Income Tax Department:** If your cash deposits are significantly disproportionate to your known sources of income, the Income Tax Department may scrutinize them and ask you to explain the source of the funds.\n\n*   **PAN Requirement:** For cash deposits exceeding \u20b950,000 in a single day, you are required to provide your Permanent Account Number (PAN).\n\nTherefore, while there's no hard limit, large cash deposits can trigger scrutiny from the Income Tax Department. It's crucial to be able to explain the source of any substantial cash deposits you make.",
